<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      xmlns:meta="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/meta"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      meta:interpolation="true"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@quaive-layout/macros/layout"
      i18n:domain="euphorie"
>
  <tal:comment condition="python:False">
     This is the choice view template.
     It is used to display how a choice would be displayed in the client.

     view: osha.oira.ploneintranet.quaive_view.QuaiveRiskView

     This template is inspired by euphorie.client.browser:templates/choice_identification.pt
  </tal:comment>
  <body>

    <metal:slot fill-slot="quaive-body">

      <form class="pat-form">
        <fieldset class="pat-checklist">
          <article class="pat-rich">
            <tal:description content="structure python:context.description">
            Sed ut perspiciatis unde omnis iste natus error sit voluptatem
            accusantium doloremque laudantium, totam rem aperiam, eaque ipsa quae
            ab illo inventore veritatis et quasi architecto beatae vitae dicta sunt
              explicabo.</tal:description>
          </article>

          <label class="label-fragment-title"
                 tal:repeat="option context/objectValues"
          >
            <fieldset>
              <input name="answer"
                     type="${python: 'checkbox' if context.allow_multiple_options else 'radio'}"
              />${option/title}
            </fieldset>
          </label>
        </fieldset>
      </form>

    </metal:slot>
  </body>

</html>
